Class GenericModule<R extends RelationManager>

java.lang.Object
  de.fu.weave.impl.ginnungagap.GenericModule<R>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Module<R>
public abstract class GenericModule<R extends RelationManager>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Module<R>

Abstract base class for all Application modules.

A module is dynamically loaded at startup of a Controller. The modules to be loaded are specified in web.xml via “module:name_of_the_module”, where “name_of_the_module” is the name that the module itself has propagated via it’s ModuleName-Annotation. This is also the name by which a module is reffered by an HTTP request. See the about-Module for an example.

Author:
Julian Fleischer
